value.0: There's a hook attached to the end of this rope. One might wonder what it's doing here. Surely a scroundrel couldn't have attempted to fish valuables from the mass grave?
Tattered rags hang about this dry, gray corpse. The spear it's impaled on stands grimly amidst scores of bones in the grave. Graverobbers might consider him a fair warning.
These floor-bound shackles are rusty with covered with dust, but you can still spot dried blood on them. Whatever rituals took place here have long since ceased.
There appears to be long-since withered flowers on this battered plate. A sacrifice or a gift of some sort, perhaps.

Value.value: On the pillar, a message is carved in Mulhorandi hieroglyphs: "Here watches the White Crown, Osiris. Those who violate the principles of maat will face his wrath. Defile not the deceased nor their resting places, lest you seek swift judgement before His face."
On the pillar, a warning is carved in pictographs few but bards, mages, other scholars and Mulan people know how to read.
